A structure that represents a calendar date with the format CCYY-MM-DD.  This structure has an optional time zone qualifier designated by appending -hh:00, where hh represent the number of hours the local time zone is behind Coordinated Universal Time (UTC).
dateTime values may be viewed as objects with integer-valued year, month, day, hour and minute properties, a decimal-valued second property, and a boolean timezoned property.
A structure that represents arbitrary precision decimal numbers.

A structure that represents a duration of time with the format PnYnMnDTnHnMnS, where nY is the number of years, nM is the number of months, nD is the number of days, nH is the number of hours, nM is the number of minutes, and nS is the number of seconds.
gDay is a gregorian day that recurs, specifically a day of the month such as the 5th of the month.
A structure that represents a Gregorian month with the format --MM--.
A structure that represents a Gregorian calendar year with the format CCYY.
A structure that represents hex-encoded binary data.
A structure that represents the standard mathematical concept of integer numbers, e.g., -2, -1, 0, 1, 2.
A structure that represents an integer with a minimum value of 0.
A structure that represents character strings in XML.

A structure that represents an instant of time with the format hh:mm:ss.sss.  This structure has an optional time zone qualifier designated by appending -hh:00, where hh represent the number of hours the local time zone is behind Coordinated Universal Time (UTC).
A structure that represents tokenized strings.  Possible values may not include line feed or tab characters, leading or trailing spaces, or internal sequences of two or more spaces.
